{
  "_doc": [
    "Per-bank row-label registry for IFRS 9 footnote extraction.",
    "",
    "Source: built by walking the BRSA audit-report PDFs (2024Q4 + 2025Q3) and",
    "cataloguing the exact row labels each bank uses in its III/IV/V NPL",
    "classification table, BRSA 7.2 'Standart Nitelikli ve Yakın İzlemedeki'",
    "loans-by-stage table, and Stage 1+2 ECL sub-table.",
    "",
    "Matching rules (see src/audit_reports/credit_quality.py):",
    "  - All labels matched case-insensitively after normalising whitespace.",
    "  - Each label is treated as a PREFIX — a line is a hit when its stripped",
    "    text starts with the registered label.",
    "  - 'aliases' supplies extra prefix forms accepted for that bank (handles",
    "    case variations, suffix decorations like '(-)' or '(31.12.2024)',",
    "    and pdfplumber's no-space rendering on a few PDFs).",
    "",
    "When a new bank publishes a report:",
    "  1. Run scripts/catalog_audit_templates.py --ticker NEWBANK to see its",
    "     actual row labels.",
    "  2. Add an entry here matching the most common label per row-type.",
    "  3. Re-extract: python scripts/backfill_credit_quality.py --ticker NEWBANK",
    "",
    "Banks falling back to generic regex (no entry below) trigger a WARNING",
    "in the log so they can be added next."
  ],
